details.body:
Appointments and relinquishment of offices

Under the Administration of Justice Ordinance 1990 (Section 9)

Appointments

James Lewis QC to be Judge of the Supreme Court for the British Antarctic Territory, with effect from 3 January 2018

Relinquishments

Simon James Bryan QC as Judge of the Supreme Court for the British Antarctic Territory, with effect from 2 January 2018

Under the Administration of Justice Ordinance 1990 (Section 28)

Appointments

David Alexander Hunt to be Magistrate for the British Antarctic Territory, with effect from 1 October 2018
Matthew Charles Phillips to be Magistrate for the British Antarctic Territory, with effect from 1 October 2018

Laws and Legal Notices

Ordinances

  • The Appropriation (2018-2019) Ordinance 2018 (No. 1 of 2018) (ODT, 11.2 KB)
  • The Licensing (Sale of Alcohol) Ordinance 2018 (No. 2 of 2018) (ODT, 60.1 KB)

Statutory Instruments

  • The Currency Regulations 2017 (No. 2 of 2017) (ODT, 64.1 KB)
  • The Licensing (Sale of Alcohol) Ordinance 2018 (Application and Fees) Regulations 2018 (No. 1 of 2018) (ODT, 70.7 KB)

Licences

  • British Antarctic Territory in respect of a coin produced with a Blue Petrel Bird (ODT, 832 KB)
  • British Antarctic Territory in respect of a coin produced of the Lunar South Pole (ODT, 2.86 MB)
  • British Antarctic Territory in respect of a coin produced commemorating Robert Falcon Scott (ODT, 1.25 MB)
  • British Antarctic Territory in respect of a coin produced with Boaty McBoatface (ODT, 170 KB)
  • British Antarctic Territory in respect of a coin produced with Emperor Penguins (ODT, 595 KB)

Orders in Council

All Orders in Council are published on the UK legislation website, which is managed by The National Archives on behalf of HM Government:

  • 2018

  • The Venezuela (Sanctions) (Overseas Territories) Order 2018/179
  • The Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (Sanctions) (Overseas Territories) (Amendment) Order 2018/524

  • The Sanctions (Overseas Territories) Order 2018/1076

  • 2017

  • The Mali (Sanctions) (Overseas Territories) Order 2017/1107
  • The Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (Sanctions) (Overseas Territories) (Amendment) (No. 3) Order 2017/1108
  • The Democratic People’s Republic of Korea (Sanctions) (Overseas Territories) (Amendment) (No. 4) Order 2017/1277

See also the Gazette for 2016 to 2017.
